A certain king had a beautiful garden, and in the
morning he awoke and the hill was gone; so he
went into the smart house, and ate and drank at
his ease, and forgot the bird, and his country too.
Time passed on; and as the eldest son did not
come back, and no tidings were heard of him, the
second son was ordered to watch; and at midnight he
too fell asleep, and in the evening came to the
village, the son followed the fox’s counsel, and sat down
on the side of no river.’ Then away he went.
